opean languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Sempill was born about 1460, in Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland as the daughter of John Sempill 4th of Fulwood. She had at least 1 son with Robert Cochran Of That Ilk."},"et":{"about 1460–":"umbes 1460–Surnud","1460–Female":"1460–Surnud","1508–1589":"1508–1589","–1508":"–1508","1458–1504":"1458–1504","1490–1539":"1490–1539","1445–1503":"1445–1503","1503":"1503","1458":"1458","1589":"1589","1445":"1445","1460":"1460","1508":"1508","1490":"1490","1539":"1539","about 1460":"umbes 1460","1504":"1504","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1460–":"noin 1460–Kuollut","1460–Female":"1460–Kuollut","1508–1589":"1508–1589","–1508":"–1508","1458–1504":"1458–1504","1490–1539":"1490–1539","1445–1503":"1445–1503","1503":"1503","1458":"1458","1589":"1589","1445":"1445","1460":"1460","1508":"1508","1490":"1490","1539":"1539","about 1460":"noin 1460","1504":"1504","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1460–":"environ 1460–Décédée","1460–Female":"1460–Décédée","1508–1589":"1508–1589","–1508":"–1508","1458–1504":"1458–1504","1490–1539":"1490–1539","1445–1503":"1445–1503","1503":"1503","1458":"1458","1589":"1589","1445":"1445","1460":"1460","1508":"1508","1490":"1490","1539":"1539","about 1460":"environ 1460","1504":"1504","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Écosse","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Sempill est née environ 1460, à Paisley, Renfrewshire, Écosse, fille de John Sempill 4th of Fulwood. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Robert Cochran Of Tha